tip.text: We visited every night when we were in Tokyo! Friendly staff & good buffalo wings (with its tangy sauce I fell in love with). If you frequent Hub, sign up for their membership for really good perks!
The matcha warabi with matcha latte is real good if you've got a craving for matcha. $6.80 for 3 pieces warabi and quite a big cuppa matcha. Not the best but one of the better matcha fixes around! 👍
Had their Lazy Breakkie and added smoked salmon and sautéed mushrooms. It's pretty good! Just a little on the steep side. It cost me about $25++ with the Coco Water.

tip.text: The courtyard is a copy place to have a cup of coffee over breakfast. Or a bottle of craft beer.
Cool promotions on weekdays! On Monday, with 2 main course ordered there's chicken wings for free. Really crispy and stayed that way till we finished our pasta! Pasta portions were huge too! 😁👍
The Harakiri is perfect for ladies who are craving for a sweet drink tinged with a mild taste of vodka.
The tomyum seafood pasta is a must try! Tangy and refreshing, at only $10 a plate after 10pm during promotion!

Pretty awesome eggs benedict! And a free bread bowl to come with. Those freshly made bread are also to die for.
